			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I also found out there are TWO Jyle Windshots. The one in the inn by the docks is actually a rogue from the guild under the inn masquerading as Jyle. He asks for 2 GP and your guild tunic. The REAL Jyle is in the inn near the Freeport Militia House and only asks for a small lantern which costs 6sp and change. There are a lot of merchants selling LARGE lanterns which will NOT work. I found one in the Office of the People selling smalls. I think that the wood you get from either Jyle will work though, since I got both and they stacked which they probably would not do if they were not the same item. My pack combined fine when I got all the components together and Maesyn gave me my Treant wood staff when I handed it to him, so I don't think it matters, except once you use your guild tunic, you can't get another so you have to go to the other Jyle if your combine fails.
				</font>
