	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Enough already...<BR>
<BR>
I ignored the many posts of people telling me not to attempt this bow with under 200 fletching skill and you should too.  My half elf ranger with 81 WIS and 75 INT made my first trueshot at 135 fletching after 10 attempts.  I have since made six more trueshots between skill 135 and 151 where I am now, usually succeed 1 out of every three tries.  Just stock up on lots of treant wood and dwarven wire first so you don't have to repeat that part of the quest.  Don't waste your plat getting your fletching to 200 before even attempting the bow!  I sold 5 of the trueshots and the plat is now paying for my fletching skill!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
