	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Questions Answered:<BR>
1.) Don't bother trying this unless your fletching is extremely high (over 150, at least).  The trivial on the Trueshot is 235, so anything under 200 and you will likely fail on the attempt 9 times out of 10.<BR>
2.) Micro servos ARE stackable.  The only components and parts required throughout this quest that are NOT stackable are the lanterns, kiola nuts, and planing tools.<BR>
3.) ANY race/class can do this quest...it just requires a high fletching skill.  (I am a high elf cleric w/ fletching at 135, WIS 159, INT 107.)<BR>
4.) You need TWO micro servos per fletching attempt on the Trueshot.  ONE servo to combine in the pack given to you by Maesyn Trueshot, and ONE servo to combine in your fletching kit after you receive the Treant Bow Staff from Maesyn.<BR>
5.) Micro servos drop off the ROGUE CLOCKWORKS in Steamfont...both the small ones near the three windmills and the larger ones near the Minotaur Cave.  They do not drop each time, so be prepared to spend some time there gathering them.<BR>
6.) Micro servos are NO DROP.  Dwarven Wire is NO DROP.<BR>
7.) JYLE Windshot (second floor of the Hogcaller's Inn in West Freeport, in the first room on the left after going up the stairs) gives you WOODEN SHARDS in exchange for a Small Lantern, not Treant Wood.  He will sometimes give a Wooden Heart...if you get this and are not going to do the Raincaller upgrade to the Trueshot, delete it because it is NO DROP.<BR>
8.) After obtaining the Treant Bow Staff from Maesyn Trueshot, the components you need to combine in your fletching kit are: (1) Treant Bow Staff, (2) Dwarven Wire, (3) Micro Servo, and (4) Planing Tool.  A failed attempt will return another Planing Tool, a successful attempt will return a Trueshot Longbow.<BR>
9.) The person that posted that &quot;the mathematical odds that you will succeed within eight attempts with fletching at 106&quot; is patently WRONG.  With my current skills (fletching 135, WIS 159, INT 107), I have attempted the Trueshot approximately seventeen times and have failed on all attempts.  A wood elf ranger friend of mine with fletching at 150 (WIS &amp; INT over 100) has attempted it eleven times and failed all eleven times.  YOU MUST HAVE VERY HIGH FLETCHING, OR YOU ARE JUST WASTING YOUR TIME.<BR>
10.) One person stated that you do not give lanterns to Jyle Windshot, you give him your newbie tunic.  Well, since you only get ONE tunic and you need MULTIPLE pieces of Wooden Shards to do more than one attempt at this quest, that seems rather ridiculous, yes?  You give SMALL LANTERNS (one at a time, or up to four at a time) to JYLE WINDSHOT in the HOGCALLER'S INN in WEST FREEPORT.  He will give you back Wooden Shards, or a Wooden Heart (no drop, used for Raincaller upgrade to the Trueshot bow).  Small Lanterns can be purchased from the Coalition of Trade Folk in North Freeport, and are not stackable.<BR>
12.) Someone posted that they received Dwarven Wire from Trantor Everhot in Kaladim by giving him only ONE Tumpy Tonic.  The person before this poster obviously gave Trantor too many Tonics.  Trantor requires TWO Tumpy Tonics in order to give you one Length of Dwarven Wire.<BR>
13.) You DO NOT get the Treant Bow Staff from Jyle Windshot.  The Treant Bow Staff is given to you by Maesyn Trueshot (Faydark's Champions, in Kelethin) after going through his dialogue, receiving a bag, and combining one spiderling silk, one micro servo, one dwarven wire, and one wooden shard in that bag, pressing COMBINE, and giving the resulting bag back to Maesyn.<BR>
14.) There is no way to transfer NO DROP items from one character to another.  That is why they are called NO DROP.<BR>
15.) You do not need your newbie ranger tunic for this quest.<BR>
16.) To get the component bag from Maesyn Trueshot, HAIL him.  He rattles on about something.  Say, &quot;WHAT TRUESHOT LONGBOW&quot; and he rattles on again.  Say, &quot;I WILL GATHER MATERIALS&quot; and he gives you the component bag.  Or you can just walk up to him and say, &quot;I will gather materials&quot; and he will give you the component bag.<BR>
17.) Since fletching maxes at over 200, a skill level of 100 isn't really considered to be &quot;master&quot; fletching.  The EQ-terminology for 101 being &quot;master&quot; is rather incongruous.<BR>
18.) The TRIVIAL for the Trueshot is 235.  235.  235.  235.  Has that sunk in yet?  Try making ANYTHING else that trivializes at or near 235, see how often you succeed, and that will give you an idea of how often you will succeed at attempting the Trueshot bow.<BR>
19.) The average (&quot;market&quot;) price for a Trueshot Longbow is 200pp.  They range in price from 100pp to 400pp, depending on who is selling, who is buying, and how desperate you are to get one.<BR>
20.) The Trueshot Discipline for rangers is available at, I believe, level 51.<BR>
<BR>
Simple Quest Run-Down:<BR>
1.) Start in North Freeport w/ several empty backpacks.<BR>
2.) Go to the Coalition of Trade Folk in North Freeport and buy at least 16 Small Lanterns.<BR>
3.) Go to West Freeport, to the Hogcaller's Inn.  Go to the second floor of the inn, take the first left, enter the first room on the left.  Here you will find Jyle Windshot.<BR>
4.) Give Jyle Windshot up to four small lanterns at a time.  He will give you either Wooden Shards or a Wooden Heart.  The Wooden Heart is for the Raincaller upgrade to the Trueshot, so delete it if you aren't going to do that quest.  You need ONE Wooden Shard per Trueshot fletching attempt.<BR>
5.) Go to East Freeport and get on the boat to Butcherblock.<BR>
6.) At the boat stop in Ocean of Tears (Tegea Prendyn is on the dock) get off the boat, go in the first hut (facing the dock) and purchase at least 16 kiola nuts from the first vendor on the left.  RUN back to the boat or sit down and wait for the next one if you miss it.<BR>
7.) Disembark from the boat in Butcherblock and go to Kaladim.<BR>
8.) Go to Irontoe's Eats.  Give one flask of water and one kiola nut to Tumpy Irontoe (you can give him 2 nuts and 2 flasks at a time) and he will give you a Tumpy Tonic for each nut/flask.<BR>
9.) Find Trantor Everhot.  Usually at Everhot's Forge or somewhere close by.  Give him TWO Tumpy Tonics at a time and he will give you ONE Length of Dwarven Wire (the wire is No Drop).  You will need TWO Dwarven Wires per Trueshot fletching attempt.<BR>
10.) Go to Steamfont.  Kill Rogue Clockworks (near the windmills or the Mino caves).  Collect MICRO SERVOS.  You will need TWO Micro Servos per Trueshot fletching attempt.<BR>
11.) While you are killing Rogue Clockworks, also kill spiderlings and collect spiderling silk.  You will need ONE spiderling silk per Trueshot fletching attempt.  (You can also kill spiderlings in Greater Faydark.)<BR>
12.) Go to Kelethin in Greater Faydark.  Find Faydark's Champions, and see Maesyn Trueshot.  Say to him, &quot;I will gather materials.&quot;  He will give you a component bag.<BR>
13.) In the component bag, put (1) one dwarven wire, (2) one spiderling silk, (3) one wooden shard, and (4) one micro servo.  Hit COMBINE, and give the resulting bag back to Maesyn.  He will give you a TREANT BOW STAFF.<BR>
14.) In a fletching kit, put the Treant Bow Staff, one micro servo, one dwarven wire, and one planing tool (sold by a gal standing next to a wheelbarrow near the Kelethin rogue's guild).  Press COMBINE.<BR>
15.) A FAILURE yields a planing tool.  A SUCCESS yields a Trueshot Longbow.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
