				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				FYI.  I am in the middle of doing this quest.  Well, the beginning actually.  I've decided to get the micro servos first since that is the item that takes the most time and uncertainty, just in case I give up I don't want to waste time and plat on stupid nuts.  To cut to the chase, the widely quoted portion from eqranger.com about killing rogue clockworks is not entirely true.  Yes they are tough (i'm sure the lvl 10-12 is pretty accurate) but they are not the only place to get micro servos.  Before I discovered the rogue clockworks by the windmills I was killing runaway clockworks or something to that effect near where the crossroads are in front of Ak'Anon and over by where the stone pillars are with the druid selling spells.  These clockworks con green for me and are about the equivalent of killing a spiderling.  I just started last night and have thus far found 2 micro servos.  Just thought I would post this for all the low level rangers out there so you don't have to get yourself killed trying to take down the big bad rogue clockworks.  But beware of BuggaButt or whatever his name is, I ran into him at level 13 and he brought the smack down on me.  Happy hunting everyone, and may Tunare bless you with a monsoon of micro servos.  (and if he does, send me a tell so i can buy some off you ;-) )<BR>
<BR>
Azzuron<BR>
Ranger of the 13th Season<BR>
Guardian of Tunare's Glade<BR>
Druzzil Ro
